author: Brandon Wenerd
title: How Filthy Is This John Hopkins Lacrosse Hidden Ball Goal?
text:
Joel Tinney @5tinman21 fools everyone & scores on a hidden ball trick pic.twitter.com/sclLahKUwd 
— Lacrosse Film Room (@LaxFilmRoom) February 7, 2017 

No hype quite like lacrosse season hype. Joel Tinney, a junior from Canada at Hopkins, just pulled off this beautiful hidden ball trick against the Naval Academy. Defense was hitting the snooze button when he ripped a wide-open goal.
Sexy as hell. Still have a couple more weeks of winter but damn it’s nice to see lax back.

[H/T: Jordie ]
